🔷 Explanation of Architecture
🔹 1. EC2 Instance (Primary - AZ-1)
Hosts static website using Apache
Stores website files in EBS volume
🔹 2. EBS Volume
Used for storing website data
Attached to EC2 instance
🔹 3. Snapshot & AMI
Snapshot → Backup of data
AMI → Backup of full instance
Used for recovery
🔹 4. Amazon S3
Stores backup data securely
Bucket is private
Used for additional backup layer
🔹 5. EC2 Instance (Secondary - AZ-2)
Launched using AMI
Runs in different Availability Zone
Ensures high availability
🔥 Key Features

✅ High availability across AZs
✅ Backup using Snapshot & AMI
✅ Secure storage in S3
✅ Same website replication
✅ Disaster recovery ready
